Aston Villa have beaten Arsenal to the signing of Norwich City midfielder, Emiliano Buendia, according to Sky Sports. The Midlands club have agreed a club-record £33m fee with the Canaries. The 24-year-old is has now completed a medical in Argentina. The proposed move also set to be a selling record for Norwich, who had also rejected an offer from Arsenal. Norwich City seal return to Premier League It is believed the fee could rise to nearly £40m with bonus add-ons. Buendia was named Championship player of the season for 2020/2021 following their promotion to Premier League. He scored 15 goals and registered 16 assists, creating more chances than any other player in the
division. EPL: Man Utd delay Man City’s title celebrations with Villa win